---
import Layout from '../../Layouts/Layout.astro';
import DemoButton from '../../components/DemoButton.svelte';
import YouTubeDemo from '../../components/YouTubeDemo.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Tyler Teuber | MultiTracks Application" description="Frontend Developer application for MultiTracks.com — worship technology, audio engineering, and modern web development.">

<!-- Fixed Navigation -->
<nav id="navbar">
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="#hero" class="nav-logo">TT</a>
    <div class="nav-links" id="navLinks">
      <a href="#letter">Why MultiTracks</a>
      <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
      <a href="#experience">Experience</a>
      <a href="#skills">Skills</a>
      <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
    </div>
    <button class="hamburger" id="hamburger" aria-label="Toggle menu">
      <span></span>
      <span></span>
      <span></span>
    </button>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- Mobile Menu Overlay -->
<div class="mobile-menu" id="mobileMenu">
  <a href="#letter" class="mobile-link">Why MultiTracks</a>
  <a href="#projects" class="mobile-link">Projects</a>
  <a href="#experience" class="mobile-link">Experience</a>
  <a href="#skills" class="mobile-link">Skills</a>
  <a href="#contact" class="mobile-link">Contact</a>
</div>

<!-- Hero -->
<section id="hero">
  <div class="hero-content reveal">
    <span class="label">Application for Frontend Developer</span>
    <h1>Tyler Teuber</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Frontend Developer &middot; Worship Guitarist &middot; Audio Tech</p>
    <p class="tagline">Building technology that serves the church — because I set up MultiTracks at mine.</p>
    <div class="portrait-wrap">
      <img src="/Images/Portrait.jpg" alt="Tyler Teuber" class="portrait" />
    </div>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="#projects" class="btn btn-primary">See My Work</a>
      <a href="#letter" class="btn btn-secondary">Why MultiTracks?</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Personal Letter -->
<section id="letter">
  <div class="container narrow reveal">
    <span class="section-label">A Note to the Team</span>
    <h2>Why MultiTracks</h2>
    <div class="letter-body">
      <p>When I joined my church plant, they weren't using MultiTracks. I saw how it would improve our worship experience, so I advocated for adding it and personally implemented it — integrating Playback with Planning Center and ProPresenter. Over a year later, our team relies on Playback, ChartBuilder, and RehearsalMix every week, and we love it. I know your products because I use them every Sunday.</p>
      <p>That experience of implementing MultiTracks at my church showed me something: the best tools don't demand attention, they quietly remove friction so people can focus on what matters. I saw it again when I built the Sermon Slide Generator for our staff — a tool that turns sermon notes into formatted PDF slides in seconds, replacing hours of manual work. Watching purposeful software give people their time back is exactly what draws me to MultiTracks' mission.</p>
      <p>I play electric guitar on the worship team and volunteer on the tech team, especially audio. So I understand the end user deeply — I know what it feels like to be setting up Sunday morning and need technology that just works. Beyond that, I'm genuinely excited by MultiTracks' emphasis on Agentic Coding and AI-first development. That's already my daily workflow — I build with Claude Code every day, and I see enormous potential in applying those patterns to worship technology.</p>
      <p>I want to bring my unique intersection of audio technology, frontend development, and hands-on MultiTracks experience to help your team continue delivering tools that serve worship teams around the world.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Projects -->
<section id="projects">
  <div class="container reveal">
    <span class="section-label">Selected Work</span>
    <h2>Projects</h2>
    <div class="projects-grid">

      <!-- Sermon Slide Generator -->
      <div class="project-card reveal">
        <div class="project-image">
          <img src="/Images/SermonSlides/SermonSlides.png" alt="Sermon Slide Generator" />
        </div>
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Sermon Slide Generator</h3>
          <p class="project-context">Built for The Redemption Church</p>
          <p>A tool that transforms raw sermon notes into polished, branded slide presentations in seconds. Built to solve a real pain point for our church media team — replacing hours of manual formatting with a single automated workflow. The Python backend parses sermon structure and applies consistent styling, while the web frontend provides an intuitive interface for non-technical volunteers.</p>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tag">HTML</span>
            <span class="tag">CSS</span>
            <span class="tag">JavaScript</span>
            <span class="tag">Automation</span>
          </div>
          <a href="https://github.com/TTeuber/Sermon_Slides_Generator" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-btn">See Code</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Synthesizer VST -->
      <div class="project-card reveal">
        <div class="project-image">
          <img src="/Images/Synth/Synth.png" alt="Synthesizer VST Plugin" />
        </div>
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Synthesizer VST Plugin</h3>
          <p class="project-context">Audio Technology + Creative UI</p>
          <p>A fully functional software synthesizer built with the JUCE framework in C++. Features a gesture-based user interface that breaks away from traditional knob-and-slider paradigms, making sound design more intuitive and expressive. Demonstrates deep understanding of audio signal processing, real-time DSP, and crafting interfaces that serve creative workflows.</p>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">C++</span>
            <span class="tag">JUCE</span>
            <span class="tag">DSP</span>
            <span class="tag">Audio</span>
            <span class="tag">UI Design</span>
          </div>
          <DemoButton client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
      <YouTubeDemo client:load />

      <!-- Content Blocker -->
      <div class="project-card reveal">
        <div class="project-image">
          <img src="/Images/Blocker/BlockScreen.png" alt="Content Blocker" />
        </div>
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Content Blocker</h3>
          <p class="project-context">Multi-Component System</p>
          <p>A comprehensive content blocking system spanning a React web dashboard, Flask API backend, Python system-level service, and TypeScript browser extension. Designed with a modular architecture where each component communicates through well-defined interfaces. Demonstrates full-stack thinking — from low-level system scripting to polished frontend interfaces.</p>
          <div class="tags">
            <span class="tag">Python</span>
            <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
            <span class="tag">React</span>
            <span class="tag">Flask</span>
            <span class="tag">Browser Extension</span>
          </div>
          <a href="https://github.com/TTeuber/HyprBlocker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-btn">See Code</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

